Johannesburg - A fatal crash between a bakkie and minibus taxi in Walkerville left three people dead and 11 others injured. The crash occurred on Tuesday night at the intersection of R82 and 2nd Road. ER24's Russel Meiring said when they arrived at the scene, they found several people scattered everyone around the scene. "Paramedics found that two men in the taxi and one in the bakkie had sustained numerous, fatal injuries. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for them and they were declared dead. "Eleven other patients were attended to on the scene. Three were found to be in a critical condition while eight others had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate," he said. "The patients were treated for their injuries and the critically injured provided with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, one of the critically injured men was airlifted by a private medical helicopter to a nearby hospital. The remaining patients were transported by ambulance to nearby hospitals," he said. The Star tried to speak to the police to get to the bottom of what caused the accident. However, they were unreachable. The Star